Assertion functions in TypeScript allow you to create custom type guards using the asserts keyword. This helps ensure that a value meets certain conditions before proceeding. For example:

```typescript
function assertIsString(value: unknown): asserts value is string {
    if (typeof value !== 'string') {
        throw new Error('Value is not a string');
    }
}
```

This approach can improve the clarity of your type checks.
